uality\nThe Cloud Stinger 2 Core comes equipped with high-quality 40mm directional drivers that are tuned to provide enhanced bass and clear, crisp sound. This makes it easy to hear in-game sound effects and conversations, and the swivel-to-mute microphone ensures that you can easily adjust the volume without having to navigate menus.\n## Quality-of-Life Features\nThe HyperX Cloud Stinger 2 Core also comes with a range of quality-of-life features that make it easy to use and control. The convenient swivel-to-mute microphone allows you to easily mute the microphone without having to unplug it, while the audio controls are located right on the headset itself, making it easy to adjust the volume without having to get up.\n## Lightweight Construction\nAt just 275 grams, the Cloud Stinger 2 Core is incredibly lightweight and comfortable to wear for prolonged gaming sessions. Its durable construction and adjustable solid steel slider make it a reliable choice, while the HyperX signature memory foam ensures that it is comfortable to wear for hours at a time.\nOverall, the HyperX Cloud Stinger 2 Core is an excellent choice for any gamer looking for a high-quality gaming headset that delivers crisp, clear sound and immersive audio. With its DTS Headphone:X Spatial Audio, quality-of-life features, and multi-platform compatibility, it's a versatile choice that is sure to enhance your gaming experience.", ":\n## Plantronics M70 - Noise-Reducing Mobile Bluetooth Headset - Black & White (Renewed) Review\nIf you're looking for a reliable Bluetooth headset that can handle all your calls and music needs, then the Plantronics M70 is definitely worth considering. This headset is designed to deliver clear and crisp audio quality, even in noisy environments. It comes with a host of features that make it stand out from other similar products in the market.\nFirstly, the Plantronics M70 is a noise-canceling headset that blocks out background noise, wind, and echo from calls. This makes it